// A 2/2 vanilla carrying ONLY Ward {2} ([CR#702.21a]) — "Whenever this
// permanent becomes the target of a spell or ability an opponent controls,
// counter it unless that player pays {2}." No card in the canon corpus has
// Ward, so this minimal carrier isolates the keyword's trigger RESOLUTION: the
// targeting spell must bind as `ThatObject` (the event-provenance the engine
// derives for a `BecameTarget` fact) so `Counter(ThatObject)` counters the
// spell on the stack, not the warded permanent.
Normal(
    name: "Ward Creature",
    mana_cost: [Generic(1), Blue],
    types: [Creature],
    power: 2,
    toughness: 2,
    abilities: [Keyword(Ward([Mana([Generic(2)])]))],
)
